ID: B2-Ch08a-Sleepy
TEXT: 

 "Okay, fine, you win!" I say. "But you'd better be out of here before the others wake up."
"Don't worry!" Melindra says. "I always wake up early. I'll be out of your hair before you know it!"

"Good," I say. "Let's go to sleep, then. It's going to be a long day, tomorrow."

We both fall asleep in a matter of minutes, and although it wasn't exactly the most comfortable night I've ever had, it wasn't all that bad either. When I wake up in the morning, however, I suddenly realize how much of a fool I was to believe anything that came out of Melindra's mouth.

"Hey, Melindra!" I say, as I shake the stillwater girl, in an attempt to wake her up. "Melindra! Wake up, damn you! You said that you'd be out of here before dawn. Do you see this?"

I then put my stat device in front of her face, so she can clearly see what hour of the day it is.

"It's already morning!" I tell her. "Wake up! Wake up, and cast that invisibility spell of yours, so you can walk out of the tent undetected, like you promised."

"I can't cast it..." Melindra says, with a sleepy voice, and with her eyes half closed. "Only once a day... Already cast once..."

 "Great!" I say. "Just great! Well, it's not that late, and I'm not hearing anyone outside, so with a little luck, we might still be able to pull this off. I think Flower had the last shift, so if you can just avoid her, you'll be in the clear. I'll open this tent to see if the coast is clear, and if I give you the signal, you'll rush straight out, do you understand?"
"Mmm..." Melindra says, as she raises her head from the ground, with her eyes still half-closed. "Mmhmm..."

"Okay, good," I say. "I'm going to open the tent now. Get ready."

"Wait, hold on!" Melindra shouts all of a sudden, as she sees me pull on the tent's zipper. "The silencing spell hasn't been canceled, yet!"

As I finish opening the tent, I immediately regret my decision, because every single one of my teammates are currently standing several dozen feet away from me, and they're all now staring straight at me and Melindra.

"Oh... right..." I say.

