ID: B2-Ch08a-Regret
TEXT: 

 "I already told you," I say. "I don't want you sleeping in my tent. Go bother someone else."
"Well, alright, then," Melindra says, with an unusually serious expression in her eyes. "If you want me gone so bad, then I'll go. But know that you're going to regret this..."

She then pulls on the tent's zipper, and she prepares to exit the tent.

"Wait!" I say. "You didn't cast the invisibility spell on yourself!"

Melindra ignores me completely, and she exits the tent, closing the zipper behind her.

 Huh. Well, that didn't go so well. Maybe with a little luck Kate didn't see her walk out of my tent. Actually, what am I even worrying about? Even if she did see her, I should easily be able to explain what happened. And it's not like I'm worried about Melindra's threat, or anything. She's still under the oath's effect, so there's nothing she can do to me. I mean... it's not like she can actually do anything to inconvenience me if she can't even use her powers to hurt me. Right?...
